[00:13.84]I used to know the sound of my own voice
[00:20.86]Now it echoes back like someone else's noise
[00:26.74]I built these walls to keep the cold away
[00:33.80]But somewhere in the dark I lost the days
[00:39.70]I see my hands but they don't feel like mine
[00:46.22]I trace the person I left far behind
[00:53.30]The mirror shows a face I can't place
[00:59.18]A hollow look where I used to have grace
[01:06.20]I'm falling into something I can't name
[01:12.04]A shadow wearing me, playing my game
[01:18.86]I don't recognise the eyes staring back
[01:24.98]I followed all my fears right off the track
[01:31.46]And now I'm someone I swore I'd never be
[01:40.14]A glass stranger looking back at me
[01:49.44]I used to laugh without rehearsing it
[01:56.44]Now every smile feels counterfeit
